# Alembic Migrations

This folder contains database migration scripts for the AI Customer Support Automation Agent.

## Setup

Alembic is pre-configured to read `DATABASE_URL` from `.env` via `config/settings.py`.
No manual edits to `alembic.ini` are needed for local development.

## Common Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `alembic upgrade head` | Apply all pending migrations (run this after pulling new code) |
| `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"` | Generate a new migration from model changes |
| `alembic downgrade -1` | Roll back the last migration |
| `alembic downgrade base` | Roll back all migrations (resets DB schema) |
| `alembic history` | Show migration history |
| `alembic current` | Show current applied revision |

## Workflow for Model Changes

1. Edit `database/models.py`
2. Run `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "short description of change"`
3. Review the generated file in `alembic/versions/`
4. Run `alembic upgrade head` to apply

## Database

- **Local development:** SQLite at `data/support_agent.db`
- **Production:** PostgreSQL on Amazon RDS — set `DATABASE_URL` in the production environment

